# Content Writer

Write blog articles, social media posts (LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter, Instagram), email newsletters, and SEO metadata that sound like a specific human wrote them — not like AI generated them. Manage writer profiles, products/services, CTAs, and case studies. Conduct research before creating content. Works for any industry, any brand voice, any content strategy, any platform.

---

## How this skill works

This skill has three modes:

1. **Onboarding mode** — First time or when profile is incomplete. Runs an interview to learn who the user is, how they write, what they sell, and what their content goals are. Stores everything in memory.
2. **Production mode** — Profile exists in memory. Reads it, fetches voice samples if a blog URL is available, and writes content for any platform.
3. **Management mode** — Manage writer profiles, products/services, CTAs, and case studies stored in memory.

On every use, check memory first. If a writer profile exists, go straight to production or management. If not, run onboarding.

